Tonight I joined the Langford family as they waited for Mayor Langford’s return. My prayers are with the whole family as they reunite. pic.twitter.com/7QXIQFZTYY

The holiday season is a reminder of the importance of family, and the commutation of Mayor Langford’s sentence means that our former Mayor can spend his final days at home in Alabama with loved ones. My prayers are with the whole Langford family as they reunite.

I want to thank the U.S. Attorney for the Northern District of Alabama Jay Town, Senator Doug Jones, our federal partners, and all those who worked side-by-side with our office despite the government shutdown to secure Mayor Langford’s release.
As I have said before, justice should be fair, but merciful. I am deeply grateful to all those who heeded our renewed call for the immediate compassionate release of Mayor Larry Langford.

I am calling on the Trump Administration to act with compassion in the case of Mayor Langford and immediately reduce his sentence. Justice should be fair but also merciful. Mayor Langford should spend his final days surrounded by family in Alabama. https://www.al.com/news/2018/12/former-birmingham-mayor-larry-langford-in-critical-condition-denied-compassionate-release.html …
Merry Christmas from my family to yours! pic.twitter.com/z39rxMbHB3

This is a one-two punch for American taxpayers. First, we have to pay for the expense of a government shutdown, on top of that we’re being asked to pay for the expense of Trump’s pet project. Time for Republicans to come to their senses and work with Dems to reopen the government

It is unconscionable that Trump would shut down the federal government to secure $5 billion for a wall that the American public does not want. This Republican Congress could not find funding for teacher pay, for access to health care, or for infrastructure investments!

Unbelievable! 12:04am Government is SHUTDOWN! Irresponsible and Unacceptable! Republicans control the House, the Senate and the White House and they simply can NOT Govern!!! All over a wall!!  Shame on you for the Trump Shutdown!!

Big win!! Today, in a bipartisan vote, the House passed legislation which paves the way for the release of records pertaining to civil rights era cold cases. Thanks @SenDougJones for leading the way on this! We should NEVER give up on justice.

Trump’s new food assistance requirements destroy another ladder out of poverty. We cannot become a nation that allows families to go hungry, or denies a hand up to those in need. As a country, we are better than that.
